                369,
                239
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1. (a) A symmetry transformation in quantum mechanics is represented by a unitary or anti-unitary operator acting on a Hilbert space. The time reversal transformation "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Theta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "relates the wave function at time "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "t"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "to time "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "- t"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Prove: "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Theta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is an anti-unitary operator. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                253,
                782,
                315
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(b) Consider state vector "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| \\psi \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for a quantum system. A time reversal transformation is represented by an anti-unitary operator "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Theta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". We now consider position space wavefunction "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\psi ( x ) = \\langle x | \\psi \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Theta | x \\rangle = | x \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Prove: the position space wave function for "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Theta | \\psi \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                259,
                316,
                782,
                380
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\psi (x) ^ {*}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/66c8976366f05505b3d10716edeaf1004872e499974e01a2c4ab04f985cb3bc7.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                514,
                387,
                558,
                405
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(c) A one dimensional quantum system is invariant under time reversal transformation, and so its Hamiltonian satisfies "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Theta H = H \\Theta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". If an energy eigenstate "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| \\psi \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "has no degeneracy, Prove: it is possible to take the position space energy eigenfunction to be real: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                261,
                412,
                782,
                474
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\psi (x) ^ {*} = \\psi (x)",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/c3ea697ae90a3fd3b9a10d8b16d36b1656b2b369b498db32015b6a60e80d0d95.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                485,
                483,
                586,
                500
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "2. Consider following quantum Hamiltonian: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                512,
                558,
                529
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "H _ {0} = \\frac {p _ {1} ^ {2}}{2 m} + \\frac {1}{2} m \\omega^ {2} x _ {1} ^ {2} + \\frac {p _ {2} ^ {2}}{2 m} + \\frac {1}{2} m \\omega^ {2} x _ {2} ^ {2}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/d4bfa9c47ef9239065c658e6b7375420247bb24519d88b92a1719ac527940034.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                377,
                535,
                661,
                566
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "This is the Hamiltonian for two decoupled harmonic oscillators. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                254,
                571,
                712,
                589
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Calculate the eigenstates and eigenvalues for "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "H _ { 0 }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(an energy eigenstate could be labeled as "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "| n _ { 1 } , n _ { 2 } \\rangle"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "). "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Assume the creation and annihilation operators for two harmonic oscillators are "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "a _ { i } ^ { \\dagger } , a _ { i } , i = 1 , 2"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". Define following operators "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                259,
                595,
                782,
                662
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "J _ {+} = a _ {1} ^ {\\dagger} a _ {2}, \\quad J _ {-} = a _ {2} ^ {\\dagger} a _ {1}, \\quad J _ {z} = \\frac {1}{2} (a _ {1} ^ {\\dagger} a _ {1} - a _ {2} ^ {\\dagger} a _ {2})",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/46ad916230ff62ff6ae6f1b0f7eb6fd84ddbabb8f2e0fd54539e40689138f962.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                364,
                670,
                705,
                700
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "i. Prove that: "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "[ J _ { z } , J _ { \\pm } ] = \\pm J _ { \\pm } , \\quad [ J _ { + } , J _ { - } ] = 2 J _ { z } ."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "ii. Consider one eigenvalue "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "E _ { n }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "H _ { 0 }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ", (here "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "n _ { 1 } + n _ { 2 } = n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "). Prove that: all eigenstates of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "E _ { n }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "form an irreducible representation of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "s u ( 2 )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "Lie algebra, and compute the spin. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                297,
                705,
                782,
                768
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(c) Consider following perturbed Hamiltonian ( "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\lambda"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is small) "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                261,
                772,
                683,
                789
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "H = H _ {0} + \\lambda x _ {1} ^ {2} p _ {2} ^ {2}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/e3e8e60ff6b8a796493c3f3cc0d8c67aab8d9c322ddc993a051970ed388a7265.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                473,
                795,
                599,
                814
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Compute the first order correction to the energy for the energy level "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n _ { 1 } + n _ { 2 } = 2"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                287,
                821,
                781,
                853
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                493,
                876,
                503,
                888
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "3. A Killing vector field "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k ^ { \\mu } \\frac { \\partial } { \\partial x ^ { \\mu } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "satisfies the equation "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k ^ { \\lambda } \\partial _ { \\lambda } g _ { \\mu \\nu } + \\partial _ { \\mu } k ^ { \\lambda } g _ { \\lambda \\nu } +"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\partial _ { \\nu } k ^ { \\lambda } g _ { \\lambda \\mu } = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                232,
                156,
                781,
                189
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Prove: "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "D _ { \\mu } k _ { \\nu } + D _ { \\nu } k _ { \\mu } = 0"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ", here "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "D _ { \\mu }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "is the covariant derivative. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) For a moving particle in gravitational background with a Killing vector field, Prove: "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "k ^ { \\mu } P _ { \\mu }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "is a conserved quantity, Here "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { P _ { \\mu } = m \\frac { d x ^ { \\nu } } { d \\tau } g _ { \\mu \\nu } } \\end{array}"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "dxν is the momentum for the free falling particle with trajectory "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "x ^ { \\nu } ( \\tau )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                259,
                196,
                779,
                263
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "4. Consider following metric "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                273,
                442,
                287
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "d s ^ {2} = - (1 - \\frac {2 M}{r}) d v ^ {2} + d r d v + r ^ {2} d \\Omega^ {2}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/8be7dc2717a3ef674db739f1a32d20e932bb3333f8511135f86c879414f0e43f.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                380,
                297,
                653,
                328
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Here "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "d \\Omega ^ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is the standard metric on two sphere. Consider the hypersurface defined by "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "S = r - 2 M = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and a vector field "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { l = \\tilde { f } ( x ) ( g ^ { \\mu \\nu } \\partial _ { \\nu } S ) \\frac { \\partial } { \\partial x ^ { \\mu } } } \\end{array}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", here "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "{ \\ddot { f } } ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a non-zero function. Prove: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                253,
                339,
                781,
                388
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\it { \\Delta } l"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "is normal to the surface "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "S"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "l ^ { 2 } = 0"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "on the surface "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "S"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(c) "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\frac { \\partial } { \\partial v }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "is a Killing vector field. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                261,
                396,
                495,
                454
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "5. The energy momentum tensor for a relativistic quantum field theory is denoted as "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\theta ^ { \\mu \\nu }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", which is symmetric and conserved. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                462,
                779,
                492
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Define new current "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "s ^ { \\mu } = x _ { \\nu } \\theta ^ { \\mu \\nu }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "and "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "K ^ { \\lambda \\mu } = x ^ { 2 } \\theta ^ { \\lambda \\mu } - 2 x ^ { \\lambda } x _ { \\rho } \\theta ^ { \\rho \\mu }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". Compute "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\partial ^ { \\mu } s _ { \\mu }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "and "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\partial _ { \\mu } K ^ { \\lambda \\mu }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ", and explain the condition on "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\theta ^ { \\mu \\nu }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "so that these new currents are conserved. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Consider a scalar field "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\sigma ( x )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "which transforms under a scale transformation as "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                259,
                501,
                779,
                580
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\delta \\sigma = x ^ {\\lambda} \\partial_ {\\lambda} \\sigma + f ^ {- 1}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/330ae6e823e3681211a731923aca39f8a001cc27aca406608c7ba0f2fd285003.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                467,
                582,
                602,
                598
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "we have following Lagrangian "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                289,
                606,
                506,
                621
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "{\\cal L} = {\\cal L} _ {s} - \\frac {\\mu_ {0} ^ {2}}{2} \\phi^ {2} e ^ {2 f \\sigma} + \\frac {1}{2 f ^ {2}} \\partial_ {\\mu} e ^ {f \\sigma} \\partial^ {\\mu} e ^ {f \\sigma}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/f4128abd2413bd4ea73525c24122ff254dd9b62fcda754e50fa5a0aee6a9a4f3.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                397,
                632,
                674,
                664
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The infinitesimal scale transformation on scalar field "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\phi"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\delta \\phi = ( 1 +"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x _ { \\lambda } \\partial ^ { \\lambda } ) _ { \\phi }"
                    },
                    {
